headlines.description: Terance Mann scored 25 points, CJ Walker added 17 and Florida State upset No. 5 Florida 83-66 on Monday night to remain undefeated.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sunshine State upset: FSU knocks off No. 5 Florida 83-66

headlines.description: Jo Lual-Acuil had 15 points and 11 rebounds, leading six players who scored in double figures for No. 23 Baylor during an 84-56 victory over Sam Houston State on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 23 Baylor ends 2-game skid, 84-56 over Sam Houston State

video.headline: Baylor's Vital puts down huge slam after Jolly block

headlines.description: Keita Bates-Diop scored 18 and C.J. Jackson added 17 as Ohio State rallied in the second half to beat Michigan 71-62 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Furious rally powers Ohio State to 71-62 win over Michigan

headlines.description: Khalil Iverson scored 14 of his 16 points in the first half to lead Wisconsin to a 64-63 win over Penn State on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iverson helps Badgers hang on for 64-63 win at Penn State

video.headline: Wisconsin edges Penn State by a point

headlines.description: Isaac Fleming scored 19 points, including the go-ahead bucket, and East Carolina rallied in the second half to slip past Campbell for a 69-66 win Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fleming helps East Carolina slip past Campbell in 69-66 win

headlines.description: Mike Amius had 19 points, including the go-ahead dunk with 7.4 seconds left and Deriece Parks scored a career-high 20 points to help Western Carolina beat Appalachian State 72-71 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Amius, Parks lead Western Carolina past App State, 72-71

headlines.description: Mike Lewis II scored 29 points on 10-of-12 shooting, Eric Williams Jr. added a career-high 24 points to go with 11 boards and Duquesne beat Maryland-Eastern Shore 86-61 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Duquesne beats Maryland-Eastern Shore 86-61

headlines.description: Scottie James scored 17 points and grabbed nine rebounds and Georgie Pacheco-Ortiz sank the winning 3-pointer just ahead of the buzzer to lift Liberty to a 77-74 win over Georgia State in overtime Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Liberty edges Georgia State 77-74 in overtime

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Liberty wins on off-balanced buzzer-beater) 2017/12/04 ESHEET

headlines.description: Joe Chealey scored 17 points and fueled the go-ahead second-half run to lead College of Charleston to a 70-58 win over High Point on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chealey leads Charleston past High Point 70-58

headlines.description: Joel Hernandez had 23 points and Jashaun Agosto scored four of his 10 points in the closing seconds to help LIU Brooklyn beat Stony Brook 75-51 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hernandez scores 23 in LIU Brooklyn's win over Stony Brook

headlines.description: Rich Kelly scored the go-ahead basket on a scoop layup with 4.8 seconds left, Mike Smith's 3-point attempt missed off the back of the rim at the buzzer and Quinnipiac beat Columbia 89-87 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kelly's scoop layup lifts Quinnipiac over Columbia 89-87

headlines.description: Caleb Wood hit six 3-pointers and finished with a career-high 26 points and Ryan Betley had a double-double to help Pennsylvania beat Howard 81-68 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wood, Betley lead Penn to 81-68 win over Howard

headlines.description: Juwan Morgan scored 15 points and De'Ron Davis added 13, spurring a decisive 18-0 second-half run Monday night to give Indiana a 77-64 victory over Iowa.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hoosiers take advantage of Iowa turnovers in 77-64 victory

headlines.description: Trae Young scored 28 points to help Oklahoma defeat Texas-San Antonio 97-85 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's 28 points lead Oklahoma past UTSA 97-85

headlines.description: Alize Johnson scored 21 points, Reggie Scurry had 13 and Missouri State used a late run to get past North Dakota State 71-58 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Missouri State beats North Dakota State 71-58

headlines.description: Ivy Smith Jr. scored a career-high 31 points and had 13 assists and Axel Mpoyo got his second double-double of the season Monday night to lead Grambling past NAIA Tougaloo for a 111-95 win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grambling holds off NAIA Tougaloo for 111-95 win

headlines.description: Garrison Mathews had 26 points on 8-of-14 shooting, including three 3-pointers, and Kenny Cooper scored a career-high 18 points to help Lipscomb beat Belmont 69-54 on Monday night in the Battle of the Boulevard.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mathews, Cooper help Lipscomb beat Belmont 69-54

headlines.description: Freshman Lindell Wigginton poured in a season-high 28 points and Iowa State rallied to beat Northern Illinois 94-80 on Monday night for its fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wigginton leads Iowa State past Northern Illinois 94-80

headlines.description: Jordan Ratinho scored 17 points, including four 3-pointers, and San Francisco held on Monday night for a 78-76 win over Central Arkansas.
headlines.shortLinkText: San Francisco hangs on for 78-76 win over Central Arkansas

headlines.description: Aaron Menzies had 32 points, on 14-of-16 shooting, and 15 rebounds, and Aaron Nettles hit six 3-pointers and finished with 20 points -- both career highs -- to help Seattle beat Division III Pacific Lutheran 99-69 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Menzies has a double-double, Seattle beats Pacific Lutheran

headlines.description: Jock Landale set career highs with 37 points and 18 rebounds on Monday night and Saint Mary's beat Sacramento State 70-54 for the Gaels' second straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Landale sets career marks in Saint Mary's win over Sac State

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
